    { "risk": "Dual-write problem: delivery status saved to DB but event never published (or vice versa) leading to silent notification loss", "severity": "critical", "mitigation": "Implement transactional outbox pattern. Write event to outbox table in same DB transaction as delivery status update. A poller or CDC process relays events to the queue. This guarantees atomicity without distributed transactions." },
